on courses free of charge.79 In previous crises, globally, most countries experienced a fall in education budgets.80 But the pandemic-induced crisis is deeper. Also, the pandemic has resulted, as we showed earlier, in a massive income and health shock for many households, with increases in unemployment and underemployment. Reductions in income and the need for greater health spending will make it difficult for some families to cover education costs. Therefore, education budgets may require some restructuring to- wards school education from higher education, if fiscal constraints are very tight.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "6fa7e9a4-7eaa-4df1-80ca-79a21033d0bb": {"__data__": {"id_": "6fa7e9a4-7eaa-4df1-80ca-79a21033d0bb", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/reducing-inequality-decade-action-achieve-sdgs-and-accelerate-post-pandemic-recovery", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "REDUCING INEQUALITY IN THE DECADE OF ACTION TO ACHIEVE THE SDGS AND ACCELERATE POST-PANDEMIC RECOVERY", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/reducing-inequality-decade-action-achieve-sdgs-and-accelerate-post-pandemic-recovery", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "ac38490244c1e2c5e08e0ce7bbfd21d30f77466b65b78668544a9d5d174a2d34"}, "2": {"node_id": "36f94b85-96a5-4baa-9271-0c66cabb6435", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/reducing-inequality-decade-action-achieve-sdgs-and-accelerate-post-pandemi