ple frame. MSR applied a multi-stage random-sampling approach to achieve a sample of women that is representative of the female population aged 18 years and above. The sample size in each state/region is based on the population of women at the national level. The distribution can be seen in Table 1.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "3b1894bf-1476-474c-8fd4-a786971f4867": {"__data__": {"id_": "3b1894bf-1476-474c-8fd4-a786971f4867", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/regressing-gender-equality-myanmar-women-living-under-pandemic-and-military-rule", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Regressing Gender Equality in Myanmar: Women living under the Pandemic and Military rule", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/regressing-gender-equality-myanmar-women-living-under-pandemic-and-military-rule", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "02d71ed83a74c67ec7fc58d1bd6142cc35b1dafb360484594157bdc8252a2bb7"}, "2": {"node_id": "ace62523-efb2-44c5-a0e8-9c86ace92757", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/regressing-gender-equality-myanmar-women-living-under-pandemic-and-military-rule", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "698d9cecd588117f2ee7838c826051606a05d1a4d46962c6d209c138d9427dd5"}}, "hash": "55aa4ecf4052e0c1427645b66156398f1e17a4a3e4cb72167e303b88526a5f55", "text": "The distribution can be seen